# arvo-strategy. Design

The strategy-marker and container-projection layer. Defines what
"strategy" means in the substrate: a compile-time tag that picks the
underlying primitive container for a given bit width. No fielded
types beyond the four ZST markers. `#![no_std]`, no alloc.

Depends on `notko` and `arvo-transparent`. Does NOT depend on
`arvo-storage`. The trait declarations are type-only and the per-N
impl bodies name only bare primitives (`u8`, `u16`, `u32`, `u64`,
`i8`..`i64`); no `Bits` reference. The `arvo-strategy` to
`arvo-storage` direction is acyclic by topology.

## Strategy markers

```rust
#[derive(ConstParamTy, ...)]
pub struct Hot;

#[derive(ConstParamTy, ...)]
pub struct Warm;

#[derive(ConstParamTy, ...)]
pub struct Cold;

#[derive(ConstParamTy, ...)]
pub struct Precise;
```

Four zero-sized types. Each derives `ConstParamTy` so it works as a
const generic argument. Each implements the sealed `Strategy` marker
trait declared here.

`Hot` selects the narrowest container per bit width. 1..=8 bits use
`u8`, 9..=16 use `u16`, 17..=32 use `u32`, 33..=64 use `u64`,
65..=128 use `u128` (single-primitive). 129..=256 dispatches via
`MultiContainer<HiT, LoT>` with the smallest-footprint pair (e.g.
129..=192 → `MultiContainer<u64, u128>`; 193..=256 →
`MultiContainer<u128, u128>`). Picked when consumers want minimum
storage and have explicit width information.

`Warm` selects the ergonomic container. Always at least `u32` for
N<=32, `u64` for 33..=64, `u128` for 65..=128. The Warm cap shifts
from 32 (round 202604271346 doc CL D2) to 128 in round 202604280500
alongside the bit-width cap extension. Wider widths (129..=256)
diagnostic the consumer at Hot or a BACKLOG-tracked Warm extension
(no native u256 means the 2x logical safety contract collapses).

`Cold` mirrors Hot's container shape; bitpacking is an access-path
concern, not a container-type concern. Column storage masks on access.
Coverage extends to 1..=256 via the Hot table plus MultiContainer.

`Precise` selects 2x-logical carriers within native primitives where
available, with saturating arithmetic. 1..=8 → `u16`, 9..=16 → `u32`,
17..=32 → `u64`, 33..=64 → `u128`. 65..=128 uses `MultiContainer<u128,
u128>` (saturating per element, post-Round-B-arith). 129..=256 awaits
the same arith bridge.

## Strategy trait

```rust
pub const trait Strategy {}
```

Sealed marker. The four markers above implement it. No methods.
Const trait so bounds compose with const fns.

## Strategy axis decomposition

Round C (round 202604280806) decomposes the bundled `Strategy` axis
into three orthogonal sub-axes, each its own sealed marker trait:

```rust
pub trait OverflowPolicy { /* Wrapping / Saturating */ }
pub trait ContainerWidth { /* Min / DoubleLogical */ }
pub trait StorageLayout { /* Dense / Bitpacked */ }
```

Each axis has two ZST markers (`Wrapping` / `Saturating`, `Min` /
`DoubleLogical`, `Dense` / `Bitpacked`). The four existing strategy
markers implement specific axis combinations:

| Marker  | OverflowPolicy | ContainerWidth | StorageLayout |
|---------|----------------|----------------|---------------|
| Hot     | Wrapping       | Min            | Dense         |
| Warm    | Wrapping       | DoubleLogical  | Dense         |
| Cold    | Wrapping       | Min            | Bitpacked     |
| Precise | Saturating     | DoubleLogical  | Dense         |

The public surface (the four markers) is unchanged. The axis traits
are the dispatch backbone: `arvo`'s arithmetic / widen / narrow
impls (`UArith`, `IArith`, `UWidenFrom`, `UNarrowFrom`) project
through `HasAxes` to pick the codegen path per axis combination.
A consumer composing `Hot + Saturating` (Hot's container width
with saturating overflow) reaches a different codegen path than
`Hot + Wrapping` does, without breaking the public marker surface.

Each axis surface carries a `const DISCRIMINANT: u8` projection.
`HasAxes::Container::DISCRIMINANT` is asserted at compile time to
match `<S as ContainerWidth>::Output::DISCRIMINANT` for every
strategy. The cross-check pins the documentation table above to
behaviour: a future round changing a strategy's axis impl without
updating `HasAxes` breaks the build, not silent runtime divergence.

Per the `arvo-toolbox-not-policer` workspace rule, the axis
decomposition exists so the substrate can grow its strategy lattice
without forking the marker namespace each time. Consumer-facing
expansion (new public markers) requires an explicit design round.

## UContainerFor

```rust
pub const trait UContainerFor<const N: u8>: Strategy {
    type T: Copy + ConstParamTy_ + ...;
}

impl const UContainerFor<1> for Hot { type T = u8; }
// ... 1..=8 -> u8
impl const UContainerFor<9> for Hot { type T = u16; }
// ... 9..=16 -> u16
// ... 17..=32 -> u32
// ... 33..=64 -> u64
// ... 65..=128 -> u128 (round 202604280500)
impl const UContainerFor<129> for Hot { type T = MultiContainer<u64, u128>; }
// ... 129..=192 -> MultiContainer<u64, u128>
// ... 193..=256 -> MultiContainer<u128, u128>

impl const UContainerFor<1> for Warm { type T = u32; }
// ... 1..=8  -> u32 (was u16; now matches Precise's 2x-logical rule)
// Updated rule: round 202604280500 lifts the explicit Warm-caps-at-32
// rule to Warm-caps-at-128, with `u128` for 33..=128 and a BACKLOG-
// tracked extension above. Existing 1..=32 cells continue to match
// the round 202604271346 D2 placement.
```

Per-N impl on each of the four markers. Bands per the strategy
semantics above. Const trait so the projection
`<S as UContainerFor<N>>::T` resolves in const fn bodies. The 65..=256
range adds two new band families: native `u128` for 65..=128 and
`MultiContainer<HiT, LoT>` for 129..=256. The MultiContainer per-cell
shape lands in `## MultiContainer dispatch` below.

## IContainerFor

```rust
pub const trait IContainerFor<const N: u8>: Strategy {
    type T: Copy + ConstParamTy_ + ...;
}

impl const IContainerFor<1> for Hot { type T = i8; }
// ... matching bands per signed primitives, mirroring UContainerFor.
// 65..=128 -> i128 (single-primitive).
// 129..=256 -> MultiContainer<i_hi, i_lo> per the same strategy
//             projection rules as UContainerFor.
```

Signed counterpart. Same structure as UContainerFor; signed primitives
through `i128` and signed `MultiContainer` shapes for 129..=256.

## BitsContainerFor

```rust
pub const trait BitsContainerFor<const N: u8, Sign: Signedness>: Strategy {
    type T: Copy + ConstParamTy_ + ...;
}

impl<S, const N: u8> const BitsContainerFor<N, Unsigned> for S
where S: UContainerFor<N>
{
    type T = <S as UContainerFor<N>>::T;
}

impl<S, const N: u8> const BitsContainerFor<N, Signed> for S
where S: IContainerFor<N>
{
    type T = <S as IContainerFor<N>>::T;
}
```

Indirection trait that projects `(N, Sign)` to either the unsigned or
the signed container table. Used at the `Bits<N, S, Sign>` field
declaration site. Keeps the U / I tables independently extensible
while routing the Sign axis through a single projection trait at the
Bits surface.

UFixed and IFixed continue to bind on `UContainerFor<N>` /
`IContainerFor<N>` directly, unchanged from prior rounds. Only `Bits`
itself binds on `BitsContainerFor<N, Sign>`.

## MultiContainer dispatch

The 129..=256 logical bit-width range dispatches via
`MultiContainer<HiT, LoT>` (declared in `arvo-storage`). Strategy-driven
(HiT, LoT) projection per:

| Strategy | Projection rule | 129..=192 example | 193..=256 example |
|----------|-----------------|-------------------|-------------------|
| Hot | smallest-footprint pair | `MultiContainer<u64, u128>` | `MultiContainer<u128, u128>` |
| Cold | smallest-footprint pair (bitpacked access at column-store layer) | `MultiContainer<u64, u128>` | `MultiContainer<u128, u128>` |
| Warm | (BACKLOG: 2x-logical doubled pair; no native u256 means cap-at-128 in this round) | (unimplemented) | (unimplemented) |
| Precise | (BACKLOG: same-length doubled pair with saturating arithmetic) | (unimplemented) | (unimplemented) |

Hot and Cold share the smallest-footprint shape (the bitpacking on
Cold is access-time, not container-time). Warm and Precise extensions
into 129..=256 await the no-native-u256 design call (BACKLOG-tracked).

The cell-by-cell impl table is generated by macro across the per-N
range. Round 202604280500 lands the storage projection only; UArith /
IArith dispatch on `MultiContainer` is BACKLOG-tracked for a follow-up
round, so UFixed / IFixed at 129..=256 await that arith bridge before
their `Add` / `Sub` / `Mul` / `Div` impls compile (UFixed / IFixed cap
at 128 in this round). `Bits<129..=256, S, Sign>` is available
standalone with the storage projection landing here.

## Resolve

```rust
pub const trait Resolve<S1: Strategy, S2: Strategy>: Strategy {
    type T: Strategy;
}
```

Pairwise strategy resolution. Used when a binary op combines two
operands carrying different strategies; the result strategy is the
"broader" of the two per a documented lattice. Const trait.

